data_description.name: Federal Marine Bioregions
data_description.description: The spatial planning framework for Canada's national network of Marine Protected Areas (MPAs) is comprised of 13 ecologically defined bioregions that cover Canada's oceans and the Great Lakes.

data_description.name: Oceans Act Marine Protected Areas
data_description.description: Fisheries and Oceans Canada has a number of Marine Protected Areas designated under the Oceans Act and Areas of Interest for new Marine Protected Areas at various stages of progress towards designation. These areas are ecologically significant, with species and/or properties that require special management consideration.
data_description.citation: Fisheries and Oceans Canada (2021) Oceans Act Marine Protected Areas. url: https://open.canada.ca/data/en/dataset/a1e18963-25dd-4219-a33f-1a38c4971250
